<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="PS4" checkit-title="Taylor series">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Let <m>f(x)</m> be a function such that:
            
            <me>
                \begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|}
                f(-5) &amp; f'(-5) &amp; f''(-5) &amp; f'''(-5) &amp; f^{(4)}(-5) &amp; f^{(5)}(-5) &amp; f^{(6)}(-5) \\
                \hline
                4 &amp; 12 &amp; 36 &amp; 108 &amp; 324 &amp; 972 &amp; 2916 
                \end{array}
            </me>
            
            <ol>
                <li>Find a Taylor polynomial for <m>f(x)</m> centered at <m>x=-5</m> of degree <m>3</m>.</li>
                <li>Using the table above, find a general closed form for <m>f^{(n)}(-5)</m>.</li>
                <li>Use (b) to find a Taylor series for <m>f(x)</m> centered at <m>x=-5</m>.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
            <ol>
                <li><m>f_{ 3 }(x)=18 \, {\left(x + 5\right)}^{3} + 18 \, {\left(x + 5\right)}^{2} + 12 \, x + 64</m>.</li>
                <li><m>f^{(n)}(-5)=4 \cdot 3^{n}</m>.</li>
                <li><m>\displaystyle f(x)=\sum_{n=0}^\infty \frac{ 4 \cdot 3^{n} }{n!} (x--5)^n</m>.</li>
            </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
